<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2344<hi rend="superscript">23/25</hi>
                        </note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>, N. Y.</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-28">September 28,
                                1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I wholly agree with your pencilled note—to recite the more liberal
                            original attitude of the Japanese when they first sought the meeting,
                            point out their much narrowed position now, earnestly ask if they cannot
                            go back to their original attitude, start discussions again on agreement
                            in principle, and reemphasize my hope for a meeting.<note n="74" xml:id="d358fn74">See oral statement of October 2, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_656">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 656</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>